         <abstract>
            <p>
               Prayer of the Virgin Mary on Bartos (identified by <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS6378Ludolf">Ludolf</persName>, <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS3562Dillmann">Dillmann</persName> and <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS10747Zotenbe">Zotenberg</persName> as Berytus, i.e. <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC1833Beirut">Bayrūt</placeName>, 
               but probably from the Παρθος, cp. <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/B6QB3HZ6"><seg type="journalArticle"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Guidi1888Atti"/><title level="a">Gli atti apocrifi degli apostoli nei testi copti, arabi ed etiopici</title><title level="j">Giornale della Società Asiatica Italiana</title><author><forename>Ignazio</forename><surname>Guidi</surname></author><date>1888</date><biblScope unit="volume">2</biblScope><biblScope unit="page">1-66</biblScope><note type="url">https://archive.org/details/GiornaleDellaSocietaAsiaticaItaliana2</note><note type="tags"><note type="tag">bm:Guidi1888Atti</note></note><note type="tag">bm:Guidi1888Atti</note><citedRange unit="page">9</citedRange></bibl>), by which she delivered the <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS11023Mathias">Apostle Mathias</persName>.
              It is used for magical purposes. 
            </p>
         </abstract>
